File: Mamelodi Sundowns will face Bloemfomtein Celtic in the finals of the Nedbank Cup. JOHANNESBURG - Mamelodi Sundowns will face Bloemfomtein Celtic in the finals of the Nedbank Cup. The Brazilians defeated Bidvest Wits 3-2 in a nail-bitter at the Orlando Stadium Saturday night. READ: Celtic through to Nedbank Cup final The match marked the return of local football action which was suspended due to the COVID-19 pandemic. A late free kick by Lyle Lakay during added time saw Downs clinch the match.